////////////////////////ALPT_2630//////////////////////////
Build Advanced Person Search Algorithm Using a Multi-Field Search Screen <Enabler>

Key details
Story

As an Administration Product Team Developer working on the Advanced Person Search in IllinoisConnect, I must be able to enter search criteria through a multi-field search screen that captures the same core identifiers planned for the future single-line search experience, so that the system can support development, validation, and testing of the search algorithm before it is applied to the single-line search bar.
Acceptance Criteria

Acceptance Criteria 1 – Navigate to the Multi-Field Advanced Person Search Screen

Given that I am in the IllinoisConnect system,
When I click on the “Advanced Person Search” option in the left-hand navigation panel,
Then the system will:

Navigate me directly to the Advanced Person Search screen

Display a multi-field search layout for entering person search criteria

Provide separate fields for the supported search identifiers needed to develop the search algorithm

Acceptance Criteria 2 – Display Core Search Fields for Algorithm Development

Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When the screen loads,
Then the system will display separate search fields for the following identifiers:

First Name

Last Name

Date of Birth

Social Security Number (SSN)

Person ID

Phone Number

Address

Gender

Race

Acceptance Criteria 3 – Allow Search Using Minimum Required Search Criteria

Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I enter at least one valid identifier in any supported search field,
And I click the Search button,
Then the system will allow the search to execute.

Acceptance Criteria 4 – Prevent Empty Search Execution

Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I click the Search button without entering any valid values into the available search fields,
Then the system will not execute the search,
And will display a validation message instructing me to enter at least one valid search identifier.

Acceptance Criteria 5 – Support Field-Level Validation Rules

Given I am entering search criteria on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I populate the available fields,
Then the system will apply the following validation rules:

First Name must allow entry of at least 1 character

Last Name must allow entry of at least 1 character

Date of Birth must accept values in MM/DD/YYYY, MM/YYYY, or YYYY format

SSN must accept either the full 9-digit value

Person ID must be numeric and contain at least 2 digits

Business Rules


The system will not execute a search unless at least one valid search identifier is entered.

First Name or Last Name must have a minimum of one character.

Date of Birth must be entered in MM/DD/YYYY, MM/YYYY, or YYYY format only.

SSN must be entered as either the full 9-digit number or last 4 digits.

Person ID must be numeric and contain at least two digits.

///////// End of APLT-2630////////////////////////////////////


