/////////////////////////ALPT-2631///////////////////////////


Execute Advanced Person Search Using Demographic Identifiers via Multi-Field Search Screen <Enabler>




Key details
Story

As an Administration Product Team developer conducting a Person Search in IllinoisConnect, I will be able to enter valid demographic identifiers across a multi-field search screen and execute a search, so that the system can retrieve matching person records and support development of the Advanced Person Search algorithm before it is applied to the single-line search bar.
Acceptance Criteria

Acceptance Criteria 1 – Enter Search Criteria Across Multiple Fields
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I enter one or more identifiers into the available search fields such as:

First Name

Last Name

Address

SSN

Date of Birth

Person ID

Phone Number

And I click Search,
Then the system must capture and process each field for search execution.

Acceptance Criteria 2 – Execute Search Using Valid Demographic Identifiers
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I enter one or more valid identifiers across the available fields,
And I click Search,
Then the system must execute the search,
And return person records that match the provided demographic identifiers.

Acceptance Criteria 3 – Apply Minimum Search Criteria Validation
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I attempt to perform a search,
Then the system must require at least one valid identifier to be entered across the available fields before executing the search.

Acceptance Criteria 4 – No Results Found
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I enter valid search criteria and execute the search,
And no person records match the entered criteria,
Then the system must display the message at the top of the results screen:
“No Matching Person Records Were Found in the System.”
And keep the results grid empty.

Acceptance Criteria 5 – Align Multi-Field Search with Future Single-Line Behavior
Given the multi-field search screen is being used as an interim solution,
When the search logic is executed using the individual fields,
Then the system must ensure that the supported identifiers and validation rules align with those planned for the single-line search bar,
So that the algorithm can be transitioned without rework.


///////// End of APLT-2631////////////////////////////////////

